{"wrapper":"div#el-blog-template","sections":{"blog-title":{"type":"blog-title","settings":{"color":"","blog-title":"5 CONSCIOUS DETAILS","title_color":"","blog-title-font-size":44,"mobile-font-size":22,"alignment":"center"}},"1663872094552ff4cb":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"2cce6dad-0394-4419-91a0-d2379ffcaf01":{"type":"image","disabled":true,"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Chinti_Friends_Tatiana_Alida_1.jpg","width":"100%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}},"2ed29440-6c52-429b-ad15-66cdcb3c77ec":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"","title_color":"#000","title_font_size":35,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>Since the beginning, we’ve aimed to have a conscious approach to production and lessen its environmental impact. We know that we still have a way to go, but each season we’re striving to improve where we can. Prioritising natural fibres, our garments are made in highly respected factories. Here we highlight some of the current collection’s eco-friendly credentials… <\/p>","content_color":"#000","text_font_size":25,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}}},"block_order":["2cce6dad-0394-4419-91a0-d2379ffcaf01","2ed29440-6c52-429b-ad15-66cdcb3c77ec"],"settings":{"title":""}},"d2cd8e55-4b42-489e-a5ac-41bd8bea5b0b":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":0,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"1663868435f0c44a9a":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"1. New Alpaca","grid-title-font-size":60,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"#000000","content-alignment":"center","grid-content":"<p>We’ve introduced alpaca into our collections, a material which has a lower environmental impact than wool. Unlike other herd animals, alpacas have soft hooves and gentle eating habits that limit soil erosion. <\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/5_Conscious_Details_1.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-left"}},"ea1ee690-e3fb-4bda-8033-019456aff2db":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"16638720430f34827e":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"2. Thoughtful Trims","grid-title-font-size":60,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","content-alignment":"center","grid-content":"<p>We use environmentally friendly trims, such as corozo buttons which are made from a cellulose non-toxic material and, unlike plastic, will eventually biodegrade. <\/p>","text-color":"#000000","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/5_Conscious_Details_2.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-right"}},"166387311379593d63":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"16638731131a5bdc7d-0":{"type":"text","disabled":true,"settings":{"title":"","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":20,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p><em><strong>How were you introduced to Chinti & Parker and why is the brand such a good fit for Women for Women International?   <\/strong><\/em><br\/><br\/>We’ve been working with Chinti & Parker since 2018, when the brand launched a collection in aid of Women for Women International. I love the fact that the brand is the brainchild of two women, Anna and Rachael, who have an inherent understanding of what women want to feel and look good in. This is so reflective of the women who go through our programme. Many of them become successful entrepreneurs or work together in embroidery \/ craft cooperatives. <\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":20,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}}},"block_order":["16638731131a5bdc7d-0"],"disabled":true,"settings":{"title":""}},"166387221970bc3eb0":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"3. Organic Cotton","grid-title-font-size":60,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","content-alignment":"center","grid-content":"<p>This season’s statement tees are made using 100% organic cotton, the benefits of which are plenty – think no pesticides, less water usage, and the active replenishment and maintenance of the earth’s soil. <\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/5_Conscious_Details_3.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-left"}},"d21d0c5f-7b79-4a9a-a2a1-521c57a634e5":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"4. Made in London","grid-title-font-size":60,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","content-alignment":"center","grid-content":"<p>A portion of our collection is made in our hometown of London. This means supporting local businesses and lowering our carbon footprint. <\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/5_Conscious_Details_4.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-right"}},"34d6422a-3dbc-4194-8783-88ce5a99a4f2":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"5. Bags for Life","grid-title-font-size":60,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","content-alignment":"center","grid-content":"<p>We supplement every purchase with a reusable canvas bag to protect your garments. These bags are made by a collective in India whose profits are spent educating local children. <\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/5_Conscious_Details_5.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-left"}},"d5b6c93a-e0f9-4ab9-9fd8-aa945db21879":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"template--15486867570781__d5b6c93a-e0f9-4ab9-9fd8-aa945db21879-168562543036288bd1-1":{"type":"image","disabled":true,"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/A_guide_to_travel_skincare_10.jpg","width":"50%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}},"f4b8a39c-e285-4b8e-a509-0386ddb86d96":{"type":"cta","settings":{"padding-top":20,"title":"Shop  Essentials","url":"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/collections\/cashmere-essentials","title_color":"#000000","title_font_siz